<span id="freeTextContainer18403472751569764582">Irvine Welsh is a freak.<br/><br/>If I have to sum up the experience of reading this book in a word, it would be ‘Whirlpool’. Like an object swirling into its abyss, the characters in this novel are sucked into a whirlpool named “Bruce Robertson” and delve deeper into its grip with each page turn. If you are indifferent about this book, you might find a lot of its content repetitive but Irvine Welsh cuts right through a lot of pages with the ferociousness of Edgar Wright montages while unwrapping a new la</span>
  <span id="freeText18403472751569764582" style="display:none">Irvine Welsh is a freak.<br /><br />If I have to sum up the experience of reading this book in a word, it would be ‘Whirlpool’. Like an object swirling into its abyss, the characters in this novel are sucked into a whirlpool named “Bruce Robertson” and delve deeper into its grip with each page turn. If you are indifferent about this book, you might find a lot of its content repetitive but Irvine Welsh cuts right through a lot of pages with the ferociousness of Edgar Wright montages while unwrapping a new layer of perversity and despair at each turn.<br /><br />To call Bruce Robertson an unconventional hero would be a massive understatement. If you have read any reviews or descriptions of this book, you might find him described as misanthropic, vulgar, racist, manipulative, blah…blah….blah….but what they don’t mention is that he has an infectious sense of fun and is incredibly charming (probably not to the characters but certainly to the readers). While the fiction genre has often taken a stab at inventing it’s version of “fearless protagonist” Irvine Welsh adds his own spin to the idea. With an utter disdain for the consequences of his actions and rudderless nature, Bruce aims to live a life without fear and full of freedom. But it costs him...Dearly.<br /><br />Welsh’s prose does a great job of transporting the reader into his world. I don’t think I was ever compelled to read a book aloud as often as during this one. I wish I could get my hands on some audio book of his. <br /><br />Overall, this is a fun ride. Every bad thing about every person is funny. You just have to get the joke or get on with it.</span>
